.TH "vmw_validation_mem_alloc" 9 "vmw_validation_mem_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_mem_alloc \- Allocate kernel memory from the validation context based allocator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vmw_validation_mem_alloc
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
The validation context
.IP "size" 12
The number of bytes to allocated.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The memory allocated may not exceed PAGE_SIZE, and the returned
address is aligned to sizeof(long). All memory allocated this way is
reclaimed after validation when calling any of the exported functions:
\fBvmw_validation_unref_lists\fP
\fBvmw_validation_revert\fP
\fBvmw_validation_done\fP
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to the allocated memory on success. NULL on failure.
